 {id:"sys1",topic:"Systems",difficulty:"Medium",type:"mc",prompt:"Solve: y=2x+1 and y=âˆ’x+7.",choices:["(2, 5)","(3, 7)","(1, 3)","(4, 9)"],answer:"(2, 5)",lesson:"At an intersection, both y-expressions are equal. Set them equal, solve for x, then substitute. Example: y=x+2 and y=âˆ’x+6 gives x=2, y=4.",explanation:"2x+1=âˆ’x+7 gives x=2 and y=5.",mistake:"System substitution error"},
 {id:"t1",topic:"Trigonometry",difficulty:"Honors",type:"mc",prompt:"Convert 150آ° to radians.",choices:["د€/6","5د€/6","3د€/2","5د€/3"],answer:"5د€/6",lesson:"Multiply degrees by د€/180 and simplify. Example: 60آ°آ·د€/180=د€/3.",explanation:"150آ·د€/180=5د€/6.",mistake:"Degree/radian conversion"}
