  "Quadratics":"Example: xآ²âˆ’5x+6 factors into (xâˆ’2)(xâˆ’3), so the solutions are 2 and 3.",
  "Complex Numbers":"Example: iâپ¶ has remainder 2 when divided by 4, so iâپ¶=iآ²=âˆ’1.",
  "Polynomials":"Example: the remainder of p(x)=xآ²+1 divided by xâˆ’3 is p(3)=10.",
  "Rational Functions":"Example: (xآ²âˆ’9)/(xâˆ’3)=(xâˆ’3)(x+3)/(xâˆ’3)=x+3, but x still cannot equal 3.",
  "Radicals":"Example: âˆڑ50=âˆڑ(25آ·2)=5âˆڑ2. Pull the square root of the perfect square outside.",
  "Exponential Functions":"Example: 2ث£=16 becomes 2ث£=2âپ´, so x=4.",
  "Logarithms":"Example: logâ‚‚(8)=3 because 2آ³=8. A log is asking for an exponent.",
  "Exponentials & Logs":"Example: logâ‚‚(8)=3 means 2آ³=8.",
